04:30.353 --> 04:32.147
What are you asking Dad for?

04:32.189 --> 04:33.565
I want to wear

04:32.189 --> 04:33.565
my pajamas to school.

04:33.607 --> 04:35.316
I'm getting a scope

04:33.607 --> 04:35.316
for my BB gun.

04:35.358 --> 04:36.610
You don't have a BB gun.

04:36.651 --> 04:39.196
Not yet.

04:39.238 --> 04:41.364
Okay, but since I'm asking

04:39.238 --> 04:41.364
to build a killer robot,

04:41.406 --> 04:42.407
I should go first.

04:42.449 --> 04:44.243
Why?

04:44.284 --> 04:46.120
Because anything

04:44.284 --> 04:46.120
after "killer robot"

04:46.161 --> 04:47.287
is gonna sound reasonable.

04:48.747 --> 04:50.498
Dad?

04:50.540 --> 04:51.917
Yeah.

04:51.959 --> 04:53.543
A couple friends and

04:51.959 --> 04:53.543
I want to explore

04:53.585 --> 04:55.503
our engineering and

04:53.585 --> 04:55.503
machining skills.

04:55.545 --> 04:56.838
Sounds great.

04:56.880 --> 04:59.340
So, um, you think

04:56.880 --> 04:59.340
it'd be all right

04:59.382 --> 05:02.343
if a bunch of Krelboynes and I

04:59.382 --> 05:02.343
build a robot in the house?

05:02.385 --> 05:04.179
Yeah, fine.

05:04.221 --> 05:06.306
Whoa, that was

05:04.221 --> 05:06.306
